## Answer: Yes, per-model override works

Two approaches:

### Approach A: Add `compat` to the model entry in `models[]`

```json
{
  "providers": {
    "nyro": {
      "compat": { "supportsLongCacheRetention": true },
      "models": [
        {
          "id": "kimi-k2.6-2",
          "name": "Kimi K2.6",
          "compat": { "supportsLongCacheRetention": false },
          "reasoning": true,
